Package: safetysignal
Title: Bayesian and Frequentist Signal Detection for Pharmacovigilance
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R:
    person("Harlan", "Nelson", , "hnelson3@iuhealth.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Disproportionality analysis for adverse event surveillance data
    (FAERS, VAERS, MAUDE). Implements the Multi-item Gamma-Poisson Shrinker
    (MGPS) with EM-fitted 2-component Gamma mixture prior (DuMouchel 1999),
    the Proportional Reporting Ratio with Yates chi-squared (Evans 2001),
    the Reporting Odds Ratio (van Puijenbroek 2002), and Bayesian Confidence
    Propagation Neural Network / Information Component (Bate 1998). A unified
    detect_all_methods() entry point runs any combination and cross-flags
    signals across methods.
